After meeting with President Muhammadu Buhari on Thursday, Senator Danjuma Goje, has backed out from the Senate Presidency race. The president is currently meeting with the two main contenders for the Senate Presidency of the 9th Assembly, Daily Trust reported earlier. MUST READ: SENATE PRESIDENCY: BUHARI, GOJE, LAWAN, EL-RUFAI IN CRUCIAL MEETING Senate Leader, Ahmad Lawan and the chairman of the Senate Committee on Appropriations, Senator Danjuma Goje who are the key contenders for the senate presidency under the APC, met with President Buhari at the State House, Abuja. Also attending the meeting is the governor of Kaduna state, Malam Nasir El-Rufai.  The meeting is coming days to the inauguration of the ninth assembly. The ninth assembly is expected to be inaugurated on Tuesday. Our reporter notes that the meeting is still ongoing as at the time this story was filed.  Details later… JUST IN: Senate presidency: Buhari, Goje, Lawan, El-Rufai in crucial meeting JUST IN: Buhari, Oshiomhole, 9 governors, APC Senators-elect in crucial meeting JUST IN: Northeast Forum, others endorse Goje for Senate President, write Oshiomhole Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin